Susan Monica , a pig farmer and welder from southern Oregon , went on trial on Tuesday in Medford . 
  She has been charged with killing two handymen living on her 20-acre pig ranch and dismembering their bodies . 
  Robert Haney and Stephen Delicino were shot in the head and dismembered a year apart at her farm . 
  Monica admitted in a recorded interview to killing the men and feeding them to her pigs . 
  She said she shot the first victim in self-defense . 
 